<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Important for hidden fields</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you only want to use one entry field (only width or only length), then you still have to specify the other dimension so that the <strong>surface areas</strong> and consequently the <strong>prices</strong> can be calculated correctly. Saving the hidden fields as displayed in the following example code will suffice (cf. <a href="#image-entry-field-dimensions">Figure 31</a>, code for numbers 1 and 2).</p>
